{{Quote|Let him go. Stay on the leader.|Darth Vader orders his wingmen to let Wedge Antilles escape after Backstabber damages his X-wing|<ref name="Episode IV" />}}
"'''Backstabber'''" was a [[human]] [[Imperial Starfighter Pilot|TIE fighter pilot]] in the [[Galactic Empire]]'s [[Black Squadron (Galactic Empire)|Black Squadron]] who served as the [[Wingmate|wingman]] of [[Anakin Skywalker|Darth Vader]] during the [[Battle of Yavin]]. He was shot down by [[Han Solo]] when Vader was following [[Luke Skywalker]] and his [[X-wing starfighter]] who was trying to destroy the [[Death Star]].

At the battle, during which the [[Alliance to Restore the Republic|Rebel]] pilots attacked the [[DS-1 Orbital Battle Station|Death Star]], Vader ordered Backstabber and [[Mithel]] to be his wingman. Vader pursued [[Red Squadron (Rebel Alliance)|Red Squadron]] as they targeted the [[thermal exhaust port]], a flaw in the Death Star put in place by Imperial scientist [[Galen Walton Erso|Galen Erso]], which would allow a precision shot to destroy the main reactor, destroying the station.

Vader, along with several other Imperial pilots, destroyed or disabled the attacking Rebel ships, with the exception of Luke Skywalker. As Vader and his wingmen targeted Skywalker, the ''[[Millennium Falcon]]'', piloted by Han Solo, engaged the Imperials, shooting down Backstabber. His death caught Vader by surprise, and led [[Mithel]] to attempt to evade the attacker, clipping Vader's [[TIE Advanced x1]] in the process before crashing into the Death Star. With Vader's ship damaged and incapacitated, he fled the battle, while Skywalker fired a proton torpedo into the thermal exhaust port, destroying the Death Star.

==Biography==
===Chosen by the Dark Lord===
{{Quote|Stay in attack formation.|Darth Vader gives orders to Backstabber and Mithel|<ref name="Episode IV" />}}
[[File:Backstabber-Vader-Mithel-ANH.png|thumb|right|300px|Backstabber (left) and Mithel (right) obediently followed Darth Vader into battle.]]
"Backstabber" was the nickname<ref name="Backstabber">{{SW|url=news/star-wars-exclusives-from-san-diego-comic-con-2020|text=Shop ''Star Wars'' Exclusives from Comic-Con@Home Online}}</ref> of a [[human]]<ref name="USW" /> [[Gender|male]]<ref name="Classics" /> from<ref name="Koto" /> the [[planet]]<ref name="Timelines">''[[Star Wars: Timelines]]''</ref> [[Corellia]]<ref name="Koto" /> who served as a [[Imperial Starfighter Pilot]]<ref name="USW" /> in the [[Galactic Empire]] during the [[Galactic Civil War]] against the [[Alliance to Restore the Republic]].<ref name="Episode IV" /> During the [[Battle of Yavin]], Backstabber was an [[ace]]<ref name="TIE Fighter">''[[TIE Fighter Owners' Workshop Manual]]''</ref> stationed on board the [[DS-1 Orbital Battle Station|Death Star]] [[superweapon]] when it traveled to the [[Yavin system]] to destroy the [[Great Temple|rebel headquarters]] on<ref name="Episode IV" /> the [[moon]] [[Yavin 4]].<ref name="Timelines" />

Alliance [[starfighter]]s attacked the Imperial [[battle station]], but its [[Commanding officer|commander]], [[Grand Moff]] [[Wilhuff Tarkin]] initially refused to give the launch order for any Imperial starfighters. The [[Dark Lord of the Sith|Darth Vader]] eventually scrambled a single [[TIE/ln space superiority starfighter]] [[squadron]], [[Black Squadron (Galactic Empire)|Black Squadron]] on his own authority to engage the rebels.<ref name="Battles">''[[Star Wars: Battles that Changed the Galaxy]]''</ref> With less then seven [[Standard minute|minutes]] until the [[Death Star]] was within range to fire, Vader then encountered Backstabber and his fellow [[pilot]]<ref name="Episode IV" /> [[Mithel]]<ref name="Mithel">{{FFGXW2|set=TIE/ln Fighter Expansion Pack|cardname="Mauler" Mithel}}</ref> in one of the battlestation's corridors and ordered them to accompany him,<ref name="Episode IV" /> commandeering them for as a [[flight]] under his command<ref name="Battles" /> to hunt down<ref name="Timelines" /> a trio of [[BTL-A4 Y-wing assault starfighter/bomber]]s in the rebel [[Gold Squadron (Rebel Alliance)|Gold Squadron]] that had broken off from the main group.<ref name="Episode IV" />

===Vader's wingman===
{{Quote|I'll take them myself. Cover me.''"<br />"''Yes, sir.|Darth Vader and Mithel|<ref name="Episode IV" />|audio=IllTakeThemMyself-ANH.flac}}
[[File:Vader-Wingmen-ANH.png|thumb|left|300px|Backstabber flew as wingman to Darth Vader during the Battle of Yavin.]]
Mithel and Backstabber then boarded their TIE fighters in one of the Death Star's [[hangar]]'s and launched alongside Vader, who piloted a [[Darth Vader's TIE Advanced|TIE Advanced x1]]. Vader ordered his two wingmen to stay in attack formation as the trio made their way to the battlestation's [[meridian trench]], where the three Gold Squadron [[Rebel pilot|pilots]] where making an attack run on the Death Star's [[thermal exhaust port]], a weak point that could be used to destroy the entire [[Space station|station]]. With five minutes until the Death Star was in range, the [[turret]]s in the trench ceased firing on the rebels as Vader, Backstabber, and Mithel approached, with the [[Sith Lord]] ordering the two TIE pilots to provide cover while he destroyed the three rebels himself. Vader then successfully destroyed the three rebels without them firing on the exhaust port and then left the trench with his two wingmen.<ref name="Episode IV" />

With only three minutes until the Death Star was in range, the rebels soon attempted a second attack run with three [[T-65B X-wing starfighter]]s from [[Red Squadron (Rebel Alliance)|Red Squadron]]. Vader ordered Backstabber and Mithel to close up formation as the Imperial trio again began pursuit in the trench, with Vader destroying the first of the three [[X-wing starfighter|X-wings]]. Backstabber then opened fire and destroyed the second, which was piloted by [[rebel pilot]] [[Theron Nett]]. The final X-wing, piloted by [[Red Leader]] [[Garven Dreis]], then did managed to launch a [[proton torpedo]] at the port; however, it merely impacted on the surface of the Death Star. Vader then pursued Dreis alone as the rebel left the trench and soon shot his X-wing down.<ref name="Episode IV" />

===Final run===
{{Quote|At the speed we were going we were really hoping that no TIEs would be able to close in on us from the rear. But our pursurers weren't just any TIEs. When a laser blast from one of them melted my micromanuvering controls, I was done.|Wedge Antilles recounts being shot by Backstabber|<ref name="Frontlines">''[[Star Wars: On the Front Lines]]''</ref>}}
With almost all of the rebel starighters destroyed and under a minute until the Death Star was within range, another trio of Red Squadron X-wings attempted a third attack run, this [[time]] going at full throttle to try and outrun Vader, Backstabber, and Mithel. The rebels then spotted the trio approaching as before, and Backstabber opened fire on the X-wing of rebel pilot [[Wedge Antilles]]. The attack failed to destroy the fighter,<ref name="Episode IV" /> but severed its hydraulic lines<ref name="DutyRoster">{{StoryCite|story=Duty Roster|book=From a Certain Point of View}}</ref> and melted its micromanuevering controls,<ref name="Frontlines" /> forcing Antilles to abandon the run and pilot his vehicle out of the trench.<ref name="Episode IV" /> Sensing that one of his wingmen wanted to pursue Antilles,<ref name="Junior" /> Vader ordered Backstabber and Mithel to let the rebel go and continue pursuing the run's leader, the pilot [[Luke Skywalker]], before shooting down Skywalker's only remaining wingman, [[Biggs Darklighter]].<ref name="Episode IV" />

[[File:BackstabberDestroyed-ANH.png|thumb|right|300px|Backstabber perished when the ''Millennium Falcon'' shot down the pilot's TIE fighter.]] 
Vader damaged Skywalker's fighter but failed to destroy it, with the pursuit continuing as the Death Star entered within range of Yavin 4 and began its firing sequence. Backstabber was then suddenly [[Death|killed]] when his vehicle was destroyed by [[blaster]] fire from above the trench, having come from the [[YT-1300 light freighter]] known as the ''[[Millennium Falcon]]''. Its pilot, rebel ally [[Han Solo]], then whooped with glee.<ref name="Episode IV" /> The shock wave from the destruction of Backstabber's fighter<ref name="Yavin">{{EncyclopediaCite|The Rise of the Rebellion and the Battle of Yavin}}</ref> and the panic of seeing the [[freighter]]<ref name="Junior" /> caused Mithel to collide with Vader and then crash into a wall, while the Sith Lord was sent spinning away into space. Clear of his Imperial pursuers, Skywalker was able to successfully launch a [[torpedo]] into the exhaust port, destroying the Death Star.<ref name="Episode IV" /> The Alliance later leaked footage of the battle on to the [[DarkNet]] that showed Backstabber's TIE being destroyed by the ''Falcon''.<ref name="Angle">{{StoryCite|story=The Angle|book=From a Certain Point of View}}</ref>

==Personality and traits==
{{Quote|Several fighters have broken off from the main group. Come with me.|Darth Vader, to Backstabber and Mithel|<ref name="Episode IV" />}}
Standing at 1.82 [[meter]]s tall,<ref name="Koto" /> Backstabber was entirely fearless<ref name="Junior">[[Star Wars: A New Hope (paperback novel)|''Star Wars: A New Hope'' junior novelization]]</ref> and considered one of Vader's best.<ref name="Odyssey">''[[The Odyssey of Star Wars: An Epic Poem]]''</ref> When the [[Sith]] ordered the [[Corellian]] to accompany him,<ref name="Episode IV" /> the pilot obediently followed<ref name="ANH AD">{{Film|IV}} {{AD|Disney+}}</ref> and gave a good performance during the battle.<ref name="Troops">{{EncyclopediaCite|Imperial Troops}}</ref>

==Equipment==
Backstabber wore a [[Color|black]] Imperial pilot's [[Flight suit|uniform]] including a [[helmet]] with a gray strip down each side of the face. The headpiece also bore a [[High Galactic]] inscription on the brow. The pilot flew a TIE/ln space superiority starfighter during the Battle of Yavin<ref name="Episode IV" /> and also made use of an [[E-11 medium blaster rifle]].<ref name="Koto" />

==Behind the scenes==
Backstabber first appeared in the [[1977]] [[original trilogy]] film, [[Star Wars: Episode IV A New Hope|''Star Wars'': Episode IV ''A New Hope'']].<ref name="Episode IV" /> In the current ''[[Star Wars]]'' [[canon]], the character's nickname was first used in a [[2020]] blog post on [[StarWars.com]] revealing a [[Kotobukiya]] figure of the character being released later that year.<ref name="Backstabber" /> The [[DS-61-3|character's]] nickname originated in the [[Star Wars Legends|''Star Wars'' Legends]] continuity, where it was first used on two cards in the [[1995]] "[[Premiere Limited]]" set for the ''[[Star Wars Customizable Card Game]]'' made by [[Decipher]]. The cards also gave the pilot's designation as DS-61-3.<ref name="Black 3">{{CCG|set=Premiere Limited|cardname=Black 3}}</ref><ref name="DS-61-3">{{CCG|set=Premiere Limited|cardname=DS-61-3}}</ref>

In the non-canon [[2022]] [[Star Wars video games|video game]] ''[[LEGO Star Wars: The Skywalker Saga]]'', Vader is shown accompanied by Backstabber and Mithel's TIE fighters during the game's version of the Battle of Yavin. When Vader orders them to cover him, the two fighters and several others swarm Vader's fighter and cluster around it before he shakes them all off. When Skywalker later fires the torpedo down the Death Star's exhaust port, Backstabber and Mithel's TIE fighters "gulp" in fear and then crash into one another, both knocking Vader off course.<ref name="LEGO">''[[LEGO Star Wars: The Skywalker Saga]]''</ref>

